Overview:
Currently, researchers manually maintain and update license information using Excel (XL) sheets. This approach is time-consuming, error-prone, and inefficient when handling large volumes of data or performing frequent updates.

To minimize manual effort and improve data accuracy, the proposed system automates the process of reading license information directly from Excel files and storing it in a centralized MongoDB collection (plv_source). This eliminates repetitive manual data entry and ensures consistency across records.

The system is built using Spring Boot–based microservices that expose REST APIs for managing license data, including create, update, and delete operations. Additionally, smart search APIs are provided to enable users to efficiently retrieve license information by applying filters or entering search criteria.

A React-based rich user interface (UI) is developed to consume these Spring Boot microservices. The UI offers an intuitive and user-friendly experience, allowing researchers to easily create, update, and manage license records.

Overall, this solution enhances productivity, reduces human errors, and enables efficient data management and retrieval through automation.

Objectives:


Automate license data retrieval from excel sheet

Store dynamic data in MongoDB (plv_source)

Enable smart, flexible search capabilities

Reduce manual effort and improve efficiency

High-Level Architecture: 
The system is designed to automate Excel-based license data ingestion and provide a user-friendly interface for managing and searching license records.

Excel File (Maintained by Researchers)
                ↓
Spring Boot Microservice (Excel Processing & REST APIs)
                ↓
MongoDB (plv_source Collection)
                ↑
React UI (Create, Update, Delete, Smart Search)
                ↑
Spring Boot Microservices (REST APIs)

